                    <span>Apparently there's considerable demand on this book in many countries, given the waiting lists and the ridiculous prices people are asking for worn-out copies at Amazon and other international stores.
<br />
<br />Addison-Wesley simply stopped printing the book because it has "2000" in its title, while in fact its content will be useful and relevant for many years to come. Even if you don't write programs that exploit undocumented features, it still has great value for those curious to know the inner plumbings of the OS.
<br />
<br />I contacted the author and he doesn't have any extra copies. So please contact Addison-Wesley and let them know that you want the book reprinted, or at least offered online at Safari Bookshelf.
<br />
<br />This way we can all buy spanky new copies for a fair price instead of paying three to five times as much for beaten-up copies.
<br />
<br />I have contacted Addison-Wesley in this regard but haven't heard anything back. May be if more than a few people did so, they'll listen.
<br />
<br />http://www.awprofessional.com/about/contact_us/index.asp
<br />
<br />http://www.awprofessional.com/title/0201721872
<br />
<br />Thanks!
<br /></span>
                  
